cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the problem of scheduling advertisement delivery in vehicular networks, which involves managing a large amount of data and making decisions based on user preferences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for conflict-free ad selection, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also deals with revenue maximization, which involves decision-making and optimization, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves computational complexity analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category as well.
